                                <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                                    Nigeria's food inflation crisis is a clear and present danger to our national stability. With <strong>33.1 million people</strong> facing acute food insecurity, a new approach is required. Existing policies have failed to address the systemic drivers of this crisis.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                                    This brief proposes the <strong>National Food Security and Price Stabilization Framework (NFSPSF)</strong>—a comprehensive, integrated strategy to build a resilient and affordable food system for all Nigerians.
